svg.title: Appendix A-2 to § 1910.269 - Application of § 1910.269 and Subpart S of this Part to Electrical Safety-Related Work Practices [Footnote 1: This flowchart applies only to the electrical safety-related work practice and training requirements in §1910.269 and §§1910.332 through 1910.335.] Flowchart: Are the employees “qualified” as defined through in §1910.399 [Footnote 2: See §§1910.269(a)(1)(ii)(B) and 1910.331(b) and (c)(1).]? If NO, then: §§1910.332 through 1910.335 If YES, then: Is this an electric power generation, transmission, or distribution installation? If NO, then Is it a commingled [Footnote 3: This means commingled to the extent that the electric power generation, transmission, or distribution installation poses the greater hazard.] installation? If not commingled, then §§1910.332 through 1910.335 OR §1910.269 plus (or) §1910.332, §1910.333(a) & (b) and §1910.334. If commingled, then return to "is this an electric power generation, transmission, or distribution installation?" If YES, then Does the installation conform to §§1910.302 through 1910.308? If NO, then §1910.269 If YES, then §1910.269 OR §§1910.332 through 1910.335 plus the paragraphs of §1910.269 that apply regardless of compliance with Subpart S (See Table | of Appendix A-2.)
